5057/* Construct a call to TM_IRREVOCABLE and insert it at the beginning of BB. */
5058
5059static void
5060ipa_tm_insert_irr_call (struct cgraph_node *node, struct tm_region *region,
5061 basic_block bb)
5062{
5063 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
5064 gcall *g;
5065
5066 transaction_subcode_ior (region, GTMA_MAY_ENTER_IRREVOCABLE);
5067
5068 g = gimple_build_call (builtin_decl_explicit (BUILT_IN_TM_IRREVOCABLE),
5069 1, build_int_cst (NULL_TREE, MODE_SERIALIRREVOCABLE));
5070
5071 split_block_after_labels (bb);
5072 gsi = gsi_after_labels (bb);
5073 gsi_insert_before (&gsi, g, GSI_SAME_STMT);
5074
5075 node->create_edge (cgraph_node::get_create
5076 (builtin_decl_explicit (BUILT_IN_TM_IRREVOCABLE)),
5077 g, 0,
5078 compute_call_stmt_bb_frequency (node->decl,
5079 gimple_bb (g)));
5080}
5081
5082/* Construct a call to TM_GETTMCLONE and insert it before GSI. */
5083
5084static bool
5085ipa_tm_insert_gettmclone_call (struct cgraph_node *node,
5086 struct tm_region *region,
5087 gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi, gcall *stmt)
5088{
5089 tree gettm_fn, ret, old_fn, callfn;
5090 gcall *g;
5091 gassign *g2;
5092 bool safe;
5093
5094 old_fn = gimple_call_fn (stmt);
5095
5096 if (TREE_CODE (old_fn) == ADDR_EXPR)
5097 {
5098 tree fndecl = TREE_OPERAND (old_fn, 0);
5099 tree clone = get_tm_clone_pair (fndecl);
5100
5101 /* By transforming the call into a TM_GETTMCLONE, we are
5102 technically taking the address of the original function and
5103 its clone. Explain this so inlining will know this function
5104 is needed. */
5105 cgraph_node::get (fndecl)->mark_address_taken () ;
5106 if (clone)
5107 cgraph_node::get (clone)->mark_address_taken ();
5108 }
5109
5110 safe = is_tm_safe (TREE_TYPE (old_fn));
5111 gettm_fn = builtin_decl_explicit (safe ? BUILT_IN_TM_GETTMCLONE_SAFE
5112 : BUILT_IN_TM_GETTMCLONE_IRR);
5113 ret = create_tmp_var (ptr_type_node);
5114
5115 if (!safe)
5116 transaction_subcode_ior (region, GTMA_MAY_ENTER_IRREVOCABLE);
5117
5118 /* Discard OBJ_TYPE_REF, since we weren't able to fold it. */
5119 if (TREE_CODE (old_fn) == OBJ_TYPE_REF)
5120 old_fn = OBJ_TYPE_REF_EXPR (old_fn);
5121
5122 g = gimple_build_call (gettm_fn, 1, old_fn);
5123 ret = make_ssa_name (ret, g);
5124 gimple_call_set_lhs (g, ret);
5125
5126 gsi_insert_before (gsi, g, GSI_SAME_STMT);
5127
5128 node->create_edge (cgraph_node::get_create (gettm_fn), g, 0,
5129 compute_call_stmt_bb_frequency (node->decl,
5130 gimple_bb (g)));
5131
5132 /* Cast return value from tm_gettmclone* into appropriate function
5133 pointer. */
5134 callfn = create_tmp_var (TREE_TYPE (old_fn));
5135 g2 = gimple_build_assign (callfn,
5136 fold_build1 (NOP_EXPR, TREE_TYPE (callfn), ret));
5137 callfn = make_ssa_name (callfn, g2);
5138 gimple_assign_set_lhs (g2, callfn);
5139 gsi_insert_before (gsi, g2, GSI_SAME_STMT);
5140
5141 /* ??? This is a hack to preserve the NOTHROW bit on the call,
5142 which we would have derived from the decl. Failure to save
5143 this bit means we might have to split the basic block. */
5144 if (gimple_call_nothrow_p (stmt))
5145 gimple_call_set_nothrow (stmt, true);
5146
5147 gimple_call_set_fn (stmt, callfn);
5148
5149 /* Discarding OBJ_TYPE_REF above may produce incompatible LHS and RHS
5150 for a call statement. Fix it. */
5151 {
5152 tree lhs = gimple_call_lhs (stmt);
5153 tree rettype = TREE_TYPE (gimple_call_fntype (stmt));
5154 if (lhs
5155 && !useless_type_conversion_p (TREE_TYPE (lhs), rettype))
5156 {
5157 tree temp;
5158
5159 temp = create_tmp_reg (rettype);
5160 gimple_call_set_lhs (stmt, temp);
5161
5162 g2 = gimple_build_assign (lhs,
5163 fold_build1 (VIEW_CONVERT_EXPR,
5164 TREE_TYPE (lhs), temp));
5165 gsi_insert_after (gsi, g2, GSI_SAME_STMT);
5166 }
5167 }
5168
5169 update_stmt (stmt);
5170 cgraph_edge *e = cgraph_node::get (current_function_decl)->get_edge (stmt);
5171 if (e && e->indirect_info)
5172 e->indirect_info->polymorphic = false;
5173
5174 return true;
5175}
5176
5177/* Helper function for ipa_tm_transform_calls*. Given a call
5178 statement in GSI which resides inside transaction REGION, redirect
5179 the call to either its wrapper function, or its clone. */
5180
5181static void
5182ipa_tm_transform_calls_redirect (struct cgraph_node *node,
5183 struct tm_region *region,
5184 gimple_stmt_iterator *gsi,
5185 bool *need_ssa_rename_p)
5186{
5187 gcall *stmt = as_a <gcall *> (gsi_stmt (*gsi));
5188 struct cgraph_node *new_node;
5189 struct cgraph_edge *e = node->get_edge (stmt);
5190 tree fndecl = gimple_call_fndecl (stmt);
5191
5192 /* For indirect calls, pass the address through the runtime. */
5193 if (fndecl == NULL)
5194 {
5195 *need_ssa_rename_p |=
5196 ipa_tm_insert_gettmclone_call (node, region, gsi, stmt);
5197 return;
5198 }
5199
5200 /* Handle some TM builtins. Ordinarily these aren't actually generated
5201 at this point, but handling these functions when written in by the
5202 user makes it easier to build unit tests. */
5203 if (flags_from_decl_or_type (fndecl) & ECF_TM_BUILTIN)
5204 return;
5205
5206 /* Fixup recursive calls inside clones. */
5207 /* ??? Why did cgraph_copy_node_for_versioning update the call edges
5208 for recursion but not update the call statements themselves? */
5209 if (e->caller == e->callee && decl_is_tm_clone (current_function_decl))
5210 {
5211 gimple_call_set_fndecl (stmt, current_function_decl);
5212 return;
5213 }
5214
5215 /* If there is a replacement, use it. */
5216 fndecl = find_tm_replacement_function (fndecl);
5217 if (fndecl)
5218 {
5219 new_node = cgraph_node::get_create (fndecl);
5220
5221 /* ??? Mark all transaction_wrap functions tm_may_enter_irr.
5222
5223 We can't do this earlier in record_tm_replacement because
5224 cgraph_remove_unreachable_nodes is called before we inject
5225 references to the node. Further, we can't do this in some
5226 nice central place in ipa_tm_execute because we don't have
5227 the exact list of wrapper functions that would be used.
5228 Marking more wrappers than necessary results in the creation
5229 of unnecessary cgraph_nodes, which can cause some of the
5230 other IPA passes to crash.
5231
5232 We do need to mark these nodes so that we get the proper
5233 result in expand_call_tm. */
5234 /* ??? This seems broken. How is it that we're marking the
5235 CALLEE as may_enter_irr? Surely we should be marking the
5236 CALLER. Also note that find_tm_replacement_function also
5237 contains mappings into the TM runtime, e.g. memcpy. These
5238 we know won't go irrevocable. */
5239 new_node->local.tm_may_enter_irr = 1;
5240 }
5241 else
5242 {
5243 struct tm_ipa_cg_data *d;
5244 struct cgraph_node *tnode = e->callee;
5245
5246 d = get_cg_data (&tnode, true);
5247 new_node = d->clone;
5248
5249 /* As we've already skipped pure calls and appropriate builtins,
5250 and we've already marked irrevocable blocks, if we can't come
5251 up with a static replacement, then ask the runtime. */
5252 if (new_node == NULL)
5253 {
5254 *need_ssa_rename_p |=
5255 ipa_tm_insert_gettmclone_call (node, region, gsi, stmt);
5256 return;
5257 }
5258
5259 fndecl = new_node->decl;
5260 }
5261
5262 e->redirect_callee (new_node);
5263 gimple_call_set_fndecl (stmt, fndecl);
5264}
5265
5266/* Helper function for ipa_tm_transform_calls. For a given BB,
5267 install calls to tm_irrevocable when IRR_BLOCKS are reached,
5268 redirect other calls to the generated transactional clone. */
5269
5270static bool
5271ipa_tm_transform_calls_1 (struct cgraph_node *node, struct tm_region *region,
5272 basic_block bb, bitmap irr_blocks)
5273{
5274 gimple_stmt_iterator gsi;
5275 bool need_ssa_rename = false;
5276
5277 if (irr_blocks && bitmap_bit_p (irr_blocks, bb->index))
5278 {
5279 ipa_tm_insert_irr_call (node, region, bb);
5280 return true;
5281 }
5282
5283 for (gsi = gsi_start_bb (bb); !gsi_end_p (gsi); gsi_next (&gsi))
5284 {
5285 gimple *stmt = gsi_stmt (gsi);
5286
5287 if (!is_gimple_call (stmt))
5288 continue;
5289 if (is_tm_pure_call (stmt))
5290 continue;
5291
5292 /* Redirect edges to the appropriate replacement or clone. */
5293 ipa_tm_transform_calls_redirect (node, region, &gsi, &need_ssa_rename);
5294 }
5295
5296 return need_ssa_rename;
5297}
5298
5299/* Walk the CFG for REGION, beginning at BB. Install calls to
5300 tm_irrevocable when IRR_BLOCKS are reached, redirect other calls to
5301 the generated transactional clone. */
5302
5303static bool
5304ipa_tm_transform_calls (struct cgraph_node *node, struct tm_region *region,
5305 basic_block bb, bitmap irr_blocks)
5306{
5307 bool need_ssa_rename = false;
5308 edge e;
5309 edge_iterator ei;
5310 auto_vec<basic_block> queue;
5311 bitmap visited_blocks = BITMAP_ALLOC (NULL);
5312
5313 queue.safe_push (bb);
5314 do
5315 {
5316 bb = queue.pop ();
5317
5318 need_ssa_rename |=
5319 ipa_tm_transform_calls_1 (node, region, bb, irr_blocks);
5320
5321 if (irr_blocks && bitmap_bit_p (irr_blocks, bb->index))
5322 continue;
5323
5324 if (region && bitmap_bit_p (region->exit_blocks, bb->index))
5325 continue;
5326
5327 FOR_EACH_EDGE (e, ei, bb->succs)
5328 if (!bitmap_bit_p (visited_blocks, e->dest->index))
5329 {
5330 bitmap_set_bit (visited_blocks, e->dest->index);
5331 queue.safe_push (e->dest);
5332 }
5333 }
5334 while (!queue.is_empty ());
5335
5336 BITMAP_FREE (visited_blocks);
5337
5338 return need_ssa_rename;
5339}
5340
5341/* Transform the calls within the TM regions within NODE. */
5342
5343static void
5344ipa_tm_transform_transaction (struct cgraph_node *node)
5345{
5346 struct tm_ipa_cg_data *d;
5347 struct tm_region *region;
5348 bool need_ssa_rename = false;
5349
5350 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5351
5352 push_cfun (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (node->decl));
5353 calculate_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
5354
5355 for (region = d->all_tm_regions; region; region = region->next)
5356 {
5357 /* If we're sure to go irrevocable, don't transform anything. */
5358 if (d->irrevocable_blocks_normal
5359 && bitmap_bit_p (d->irrevocable_blocks_normal,
5360 region->entry_block->index))
5361 {
5362 transaction_subcode_ior (region, GTMA_DOES_GO_IRREVOCABLE
5363 | GTMA_MAY_ENTER_IRREVOCABLE
5364 | GTMA_HAS_NO_INSTRUMENTATION);
5365 continue;
5366 }
5367
5368 need_ssa_rename |=
5369 ipa_tm_transform_calls (node, region, region->entry_block,
5370 d->irrevocable_blocks_normal);
5371 }
5372
5373 if (need_ssa_rename)
5374 update_ssa (TODO_update_ssa_only_virtuals);
5375
5376 pop_cfun ();
5377}
5378
5379/* Transform the calls within the transactional clone of NODE. */
5380
5381static void
5382ipa_tm_transform_clone (struct cgraph_node *node)
5383{
5384 struct tm_ipa_cg_data *d;
5385 bool need_ssa_rename;
5386
5387 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5388
5389 /* If this function makes no calls and has no irrevocable blocks,
5390 then there's nothing to do. */
5391 /* ??? Remove non-aborting top-level transactions. */
5392 if (!node->callees && !node->indirect_calls && !d->irrevocable_blocks_clone)
5393 return;
5394
5395 push_cfun (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (d->clone->decl));
5396 calculate_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
5397
5398 need_ssa_rename =
5399 ipa_tm_transform_calls (d->clone, NULL,
5400 single_succ (ENTRY_BLOCK_PTR_FOR_FN (cfun)),
5401 d->irrevocable_blocks_clone);
5402
5403 if (need_ssa_rename)
5404 update_ssa (TODO_update_ssa_only_virtuals);
5405
5406 pop_cfun ();
5407}
5408
5409/* Main entry point for the transactional memory IPA pass. */
5410
5411static unsigned int
5412ipa_tm_execute (void)
5413{
5414 cgraph_node_queue tm_callees = cgraph_node_queue ();
5415 /* List of functions that will go irrevocable. */
5416 cgraph_node_queue irr_worklist = cgraph_node_queue ();
5417
5418 struct cgraph_node *node;
5419 struct tm_ipa_cg_data *d;
5420 enum availability a;
5421 unsigned int i;
5422
5423 cgraph_node::checking_verify_cgraph_nodes ();
5424
5425 bitmap_obstack_initialize (&tm_obstack);
5426 initialize_original_copy_tables ();
5427
5428 /* For all local functions marked tm_callable, queue them. */
5429 FOR_EACH_DEFINED_FUNCTION (node)
5430 if (is_tm_callable (node->decl)
5431 && node->get_availability () >= AVAIL_INTERPOSABLE)
5432 {
5433 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5434 maybe_push_queue (node, &tm_callees, &d->in_callee_queue);
5435 }
5436
5437 /* For all local reachable functions... */
5438 FOR_EACH_DEFINED_FUNCTION (node)
5439 if (node->lowered
5440 && node->get_availability () >= AVAIL_INTERPOSABLE)
5441 {
5442 /* ... marked tm_pure, record that fact for the runtime by
5443 indicating that the pure function is its own tm_callable.
5444 No need to do this if the function's address can't be taken. */
5445 if (is_tm_pure (node->decl))
5446 {
5447 if (!node->local.local)
5448 record_tm_clone_pair (node->decl, node->decl);
5449 continue;
5450 }
5451
5452 push_cfun (DECL_STRUCT_FUNCTION (node->decl));
5453 calculate_dominance_info (CDI_DOMINATORS);
5454
5455 tm_region_init (NULL);
5456 if (all_tm_regions)
5457 {
5458 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5459
5460 /* Scan for calls that are in each transaction, and
5461 generate the uninstrumented code path. */
5462 ipa_tm_scan_calls_transaction (d, &tm_callees);
5463
5464 /* Put it in the worklist so we can scan the function
5465 later (ipa_tm_scan_irr_function) and mark the
5466 irrevocable blocks. */
5467 maybe_push_queue (node, &irr_worklist, &d->in_worklist);
5468 d->want_irr_scan_normal = true;
5469 }
5470
5471 pop_cfun ();
5472 }
5473
5474 /* For every local function on the callee list, scan as if we will be
5475 creating a transactional clone, queueing all new functions we find
5476 along the way. */
5477 for (i = 0; i < tm_callees.length (); ++i)
5478 {
5479 node = tm_callees[i];
5480 a = node->get_availability ();
5481 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5482
5483 /* Put it in the worklist so we can scan the function later
5484 (ipa_tm_scan_irr_function) and mark the irrevocable
5485 blocks. */
5486 maybe_push_queue (node, &irr_worklist, &d->in_worklist);
5487
5488 /* Some callees cannot be arbitrarily cloned. These will always be
5489 irrevocable. Mark these now, so that we need not scan them. */
5490 if (is_tm_irrevocable (node->decl))
5491 ipa_tm_note_irrevocable (node, &irr_worklist);
5492 else if (a <= AVAIL_NOT_AVAILABLE
5493 && !is_tm_safe_or_pure (node->decl))
5494 ipa_tm_note_irrevocable (node, &irr_worklist);
5495 else if (a >= AVAIL_INTERPOSABLE)
5496 {
5497 if (!tree_versionable_function_p (node->decl))
5498 ipa_tm_note_irrevocable (node, &irr_worklist);
5499 else if (!d->is_irrevocable)
5500 {
5501 /* If this is an alias, make sure its base is queued as well.
5502 we need not scan the callees now, as the base will do. */
5503 if (node->alias)
5504 {
5505 node = cgraph_node::get (node->thunk.alias);
5506 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5507 maybe_push_queue (node, &tm_callees, &d->in_callee_queue);
5508 continue;
5509 }
5510
5511 /* Add all nodes called by this function into
5512 tm_callees as well. */
5513 ipa_tm_scan_calls_clone (node, &tm_callees);
5514 }
5515 }
5516 }
5517
5518 /* Iterate scans until no more work to be done. Prefer not to use
5519 vec::pop because the worklist tends to follow a breadth-first
5520 search of the callgraph, which should allow convergance with a
5521 minimum number of scans. But we also don't want the worklist
5522 array to grow without bound, so we shift the array up periodically. */
5523 for (i = 0; i < irr_worklist.length (); ++i)
5524 {
5525 if (i > 256 && i == irr_worklist.length () / 8)
5526 {
5527 irr_worklist.block_remove (0, i);
5528 i = 0;
5529 }
5530
5531 node = irr_worklist[i];
5532 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5533 d->in_worklist = false;
5534
5535 if (d->want_irr_scan_normal)
5536 {
5537 d->want_irr_scan_normal = false;
5538 ipa_tm_scan_irr_function (node, false);
5539 }
5540 if (d->in_callee_queue && ipa_tm_scan_irr_function (node, true))
5541 ipa_tm_note_irrevocable (node, &irr_worklist);
5542 }
5543
5544 /* For every function on the callee list, collect the tm_may_enter_irr
5545 bit on the node. */
5546 irr_worklist.truncate (0);
5547 for (i = 0; i < tm_callees.length (); ++i)
5548 {
5549 node = tm_callees[i];
5550 if (ipa_tm_mayenterirr_function (node))
5551 {
5552 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5553 gcc_assert (d->in_worklist == false);
5554 maybe_push_queue (node, &irr_worklist, &d->in_worklist);
5555 }
5556 }
5557
5558 /* Propagate the tm_may_enter_irr bit to callers until stable. */
5559 for (i = 0; i < irr_worklist.length (); ++i)
5560 {
5561 struct cgraph_node *caller;
5562 struct cgraph_edge *e;
5563 struct ipa_ref *ref;
5564
5565 if (i > 256 && i == irr_worklist.length () / 8)
5566 {
5567 irr_worklist.block_remove (0, i);
5568 i = 0;
5569 }
5570
5571 node = irr_worklist[i];
5572 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5573 d->in_worklist = false;
5574 node->local.tm_may_enter_irr = true;
5575
5576 /* Propagate back to normal callers. */
5577 for (e = node->callers; e ; e = e->next_caller)
5578 {
5579 caller = e->caller;
5580 if (!is_tm_safe_or_pure (caller->decl)
5581 && !caller->local.tm_may_enter_irr)
5582 {
5583 d = get_cg_data (&caller, true);
5584 maybe_push_queue (caller, &irr_worklist, &d->in_worklist);
5585 }
5586 }
5587
5588 /* Propagate back to referring aliases as well. */
5589 FOR_EACH_ALIAS (node, ref)
5590 {
5591 caller = dyn_cast<cgraph_node *> (ref->referring);
5592 if (!caller->local.tm_may_enter_irr)
5593 {
5594 /* ?? Do not traverse aliases here. */
5595 d = get_cg_data (&caller, false);
5596 maybe_push_queue (caller, &irr_worklist, &d->in_worklist);
5597 }
5598 }
5599 }
5600
5601 /* Now validate all tm_safe functions, and all atomic regions in
5602 other functions. */
5603 FOR_EACH_DEFINED_FUNCTION (node)
5604 if (node->lowered
5605 && node->get_availability () >= AVAIL_INTERPOSABLE)
5606 {
5607 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5608 if (is_tm_safe (node->decl))
5609 ipa_tm_diagnose_tm_safe (node);
5610 else if (d->all_tm_regions)
5611 ipa_tm_diagnose_transaction (node, d->all_tm_regions);
5612 }
5613
5614 /* Create clones. Do those that are not irrevocable and have a
5615 positive call count. Do those publicly visible functions that
5616 the user directed us to clone. */
5617 for (i = 0; i < tm_callees.length (); ++i)
5618 {
5619 bool doit = false;
5620
5621 node = tm_callees[i];
5622 if (node->cpp_implicit_alias)
5623 continue;
5624
5625 a = node->get_availability ();
5626 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5627
5628 if (a <= AVAIL_NOT_AVAILABLE)
5629 doit = is_tm_callable (node->decl);
5630 else if (a <= AVAIL_AVAILABLE && is_tm_callable (node->decl))
5631 doit = true;
5632 else if (!d->is_irrevocable
5633 && d->tm_callers_normal + d->tm_callers_clone > 0)
5634 doit = true;
5635
5636 if (doit)
5637 ipa_tm_create_version (node);
5638 }
5639
5640 /* Redirect calls to the new clones, and insert irrevocable marks. */
5641 for (i = 0; i < tm_callees.length (); ++i)
5642 {
5643 node = tm_callees[i];
5644 if (node->analyzed)
5645 {
5646 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5647 if (d->clone)
5648 ipa_tm_transform_clone (node);
5649 }
5650 }
5651 FOR_EACH_DEFINED_FUNCTION (node)
5652 if (node->lowered
5653 && node->get_availability () >= AVAIL_INTERPOSABLE)
5654 {
5655 d = get_cg_data (&node, true);
5656 if (d->all_tm_regions)
5657 ipa_tm_transform_transaction (node);
5658 }
5659
5660 /* Free and clear all data structures. */
5661 tm_callees.release ();
5662 irr_worklist.release ();
5663 bitmap_obstack_release (&tm_obstack);
5664 free_original_copy_tables ();
5665
5666 FOR_EACH_FUNCTION (node)
5667 node->aux = NULL;
5668
5669 cgraph_node::checking_verify_cgraph_nodes ();
5670
5671 return 0;
5672}
